You are hungry! Let's cook a delicious meal. Check the cookbook in the kitchen for the recipe. Once done, enjoy your meal!

-= Kitchen =-
You find yourself in a kitchen. An ordinary one. You begin to take stock of what's here.

Oh, great. Here's a fridge. There's something strange about this thing being here, but you don't have time to worry about that now. You can see a closed oven. Oh wow! Is that what I think it is? It is! It's a table. You see a cookbook and a knife on the table. You can see a counter. What a great pairing of adjectives and nouns! But the thing is empty, unfortunately. Aw, here you were, all excited for there to be things on it! You hear a noise behind you and spin around, but you can't see anything other than a stove. The stove is conventional. Unfortunately, there isn't a thing on it.

There is a closed sliding patio door leading east. There is a closed plain door leading south. There is an exit to the north.

-= Kitchen =-
You find yourself in a kitchen. An ordinary one. You begin to take stock of what's here.

Oh, great. Here's a fridge. There's something strange about this thing being here, but you don't have time to worry about that now. You can see a closed oven. Oh wow! Is that what I think it is? It is! It's a table. You see a cookbook and a knife on the table. You can see a counter. What a great pairing of adjectives and nouns! But the thing is empty, unfortunately. Aw, here you were, all excited for there to be things on it! You hear a noise behind you and spin around, but you can't see anything other than a stove. The stove is conventional. Unfortunately, there isn't a thing on it.

There is a closed sliding patio door leading east. There is a closed plain door leading south. There is an exit to the north.
